---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: Victor Officer L&D-VNR <training@vnrvjiet.in>
Date: Tue, 13 Jan 2026 at 10:52
Subject: Aptitude Training for 2027 batch - for all B.Tech (3rd Year),
M.Tech(1st Year) & MCA(1st Year) students || 19th JAN 2026 onwards
To: <vnr_2027_batch@googlegroups.com>
Cc: mtpteam_vnr <mtpteam_vnr@googlegroups.com>, heads <heads@vnrvjiet.in>, <
sureshreddy_g@vnrvjiet.in>, <sreenivasarao_a@vnrvjiet.in>, principal <
principal@vnrvjiet.in>, <transport@vnrvjiet.in>


Dear Students,

We are happy to inform you that T&P is planning to organize Aptitude
Training for all the 2027 batch students - B.Tech (3rd Year), M.Tech(1st
Year) & MCA(1st Year) from 19th Jan 2026 onwards to enhance problem solving
skills and to teach shortcut methods in Quantitative Aptitude and Logical
reasoning topics.

All the students are eligible to attend the training irrespective of your
percentage and backlogs status. Please note that Any Campus Recruitment
Process includes Preliminary Round of Test with English, Quants, Reasoning
topics where maximum elimination takes place. Hence, you must become expert
in these areas to increase the probability of getting shortlisted for
further selection process.

*Aptitude is important not only for placements but also for all competitive
exams (Govt Jobs), Higher Education entrance tests.*

Please make a note of your batch, schedule and attend the training without
fail. Attendance will be taken in each session. Attending all the sessions
is mandatory to become eligible for placements. These sessions are
scheduled to make you placement ready and hence ownership lies with you in
learning the topics and performing well during the campus placements.

Training runs 6 hours a day at KS Auditorium from 19th Jan 2026 onwards for
25 working days. We will have 2 batches every day with 3 hours each
session. Each batch will get 10 sessions overall. You must maintain a
separate notebook and make a note of the shortcuts for your reference.

*Batches & Training Schedule: *

*Batch*

*Branches*

*Count*

*B1*

CSE-CYS, CSBS, CSE

433

*B2*

CSE-AIML, DS

430

*B3*

IOT, AI&DS, IT & M.TECH

450

*B4*

ECE, EEE, MCA

454

*B5*

EIE, CIVIL, MECH, AME

470

Aptitude Training for 2027 Batch - Schedule Aptitude Training for 2027
Batch - Schedule
Day DATE FN (10AM-1PM) AN(1.40-4.40PM) Day DATE FN (10AM-1PM)
AN(1.40-4.40PM)

2 20th Jan B3 B1 17 9th Feb B5 B4
3 21st Jan B2 B3 18 10th Feb B4 B5
4 22nd Jan B1 B2 19 11th Feb B5 B4
5 23rd Jan B3 B1 20 12th Feb B4 B5
6 27th Jan B2 B3 21 13th Feb B5 B4
7 28th Jan B1 B2 22 14th Feb B4 B5
8 29th Jan B3 B1 23 16th Feb B5 B4
9 30th Jan B2 B3 24 17th Feb B4 B5
10 31st Jan B1 B2 25 18th Feb B5 B4
11 2nd Feb B3 B1
12 3rd Feb B2 B3
13 4th Feb B1 B2
14 5th Feb B3 B1
15 6th Feb B2 B3
Students are instructed to maintain punctuality and finish the attendance
part before the start of the session and cooperate. So that Trainer will
get maximum time and can cover more topics within the given time. We expect
professional behaviour and cooperation from all the participants to make
this HIgh Intensity Aptitude Training successful.

*Note: Faculty Coordinators are requested to take attendance well before
the start of the session and look after discipline and punctuality of
respective students during the training program.*


-- 

--
Thanks & Regards,





*Victor Samuel MOfficer-Learning & DevelopmentVNR Vignana Jyothi Institute
of Engg & TechnologyBachupally, Hyderabad-500090Mob: 9848181013 /
7995658575, Off: 040-23042575 extn: 5061*
